         = \n| campuses               = \n| campus                 = \n| campus_size            = \n| area                   = \n| campus_type            = Suburban\n| campus_bound           = \n| houses                 = \n| student_union          = <!-- use | student_union_label = to override the default label -->\n| colours                = <!-- or | colors = -->\n| school_colors         = Blue and White \n| slogan                 = \n| song                   = \n| fight_song             = \n| athletics              = \n| athletics_conference   = [[Tri-Valley League (MIAA)|Tri-Valley League]]\n| sports                 = \n| mascot                 = Mustangs\n| mascot_image           = \n| nickname               = NHS\n| teams                  = <!-- use | teams_label = to override the default label -->\n| rivals                 = \n| vision                 = \n| accreditation          = <!-- or | accreditations = -->\n| ranking                = \n| USNWR_ranking          =\n| national_ranking       = \n| test_name              = \n| test_average           = \n| SAT                    = 558 verbal<br />564 math<br />1122 total (2017-2018)<ref>http://profiles.doe.mass.edu/statereport/sat.aspx</ref>\n| SAT_year               = \n| ACT                    = \n| ACT_year               = \n| bar_pass_rate          = \n| school_roll            = \n| decile                 = \n| publication            = \n| newspaper              = \n| yearbook               = \n| products               = \n| endowment              = \n| budget                 = \n| fees                   = \n| annual_tuition         = \n| tuition                = \n| revenue                = \n| communities            = [[Norwood, Massachusetts|Norwood]]\n| feeder_schools         = [[Coakley Middle School]]\n| feeder_to              = \n| graduates              = \n| graduates_year         = \n| affiliation            = <!-- or | affiliations = -->\n| alumni                 = \n| nobel_laureates        = \n| information            = \n| homepage               = \n| url                    = [http://www.norwood.k12.ma.us/nhs/index.cfm Welcome to Norwood High School in Norwood, Massachusetts]\n| website                = \n| footnotes              = \n| picture                = \n| picture_caption        = \n| picture2               = \n| picture_caption2       = \n| lastupdate             =\n}}\n\n'''Norwood High School''' ('''NHS''') is a four-year public [[secondary school]] located in [[Norwood, Massachusetts]], within [[Norfolk County, Massachusetts|Norfolk County]].  The school is the only high school within the [[Norwood Public Schools]] district and is located at 245 Nichols Street.\n\n== Demographics <ref>{{cite web |title=Enrollment Data (2018-19) - Norwood High (02200505) |url=http://profiles.doe.mass.edu/profiles/student.aspx?orgcode=02200505&orgtypecode=6& |website=profiles.doe.mass.edu}}</ref>== \n{{Massachusetts High School Student Demographics\n|reporting_year    = 2018-2019\n|total#            =985\n|teacher#          =70\n|afr%              =12.4\n|asian%            =4.5\n|hisp%             =13.1\n|nat%              =0\n|white%            =67.4\n|haw%              =0.1\n|multi%            =2.5\n|male#             =493\n|fem#              =492\n|gr9#              =255\n|gr10#             =242\n|gr11#             =245\n|gr12#             =236\n|grsp#             =7\n}}\n\n\n== Athletics ==\nThe '''Norwood Mustangs''' are a member of the [[Bay State Conference]], a league within the [[Massachusetts Interscholastic Athletic Association]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Bay State Conference|url=http://www.baystateconference.org/g5-bin/client.cgi?G5button=7|accessdate=29 December 2014}}</ref> They have a traditional rivalry with [[Dedham High School]] and [[Walpole High School]].\n\nIn 2016, Norwood explored a move to the Tri-Valley League, similar to Dedham's move after the 2015\u201316 academic year. Norwood had the second-smallest enrollment of BSC schools during the 2015-16 year with 967, less than half of the largest schools in the conference.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.norwoodrecord.com/22989/248028/a/for-the-bay-state-conference-its-a-numbers-game|title=For the Bay State Conference, it's a numbers game|author=|date=|website=norwoodrecord.com}}</ref> In October 2017, Norwood's move to the TVL became official. The 2017\u20132018 school year was the 60th and final season for Norwood's membership in the Bay State Conference.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.norwoodrecord.com/22989/306922/a/its-official-norwood-high-school-to-join-tri-valley-league-for-2018-19-school-ye|title=It's official: Norwood High School to join Tri-Valley League for 2018-19 school year|author=|date=|website=norwoodrecord.com}}</ref>\n\nNorwood High's baseball team won the Division 1 state championship in 2015, snapping a 72-year drought between titles.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Massachusetts Public High Schools}}\n\n[[Category:Norwood, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Bay State Conference schools]]\n[[Category:Public high schools in Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in the 1920s]]\n[[Category:Schools in Norfolk County, Massachusetts]]\n\n\n{{Massachusetts-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n| name                   = Norwood High School\n| native_name            = \n| latin_name             = \n| logo                   =\n| logo_alt               = \n| seal_image             = \n| seal_size              = \n| seal_alt               = \n| image                  = Norwood High School, Norwood MA.jpg\n| image_size             = \n| alt                    = \n| caption                = Norwood High School\n| pushpin_map            = Massachusetts#USA\n| pushpin_mapsize        = \n| pushpin_image          = \n| pushpin_label_position = \n| pushpin_label          = \n| pushpin_map_alt        = \n| pushpin_map_caption    = \n| address                = 245 Nichols St, Norwood, MA 02062\n| location               